igins, functions, and limits of political order in the modern international system.The book is a model of clarity in theory, research design, and the use of evidence. Motivated by concerns about the declining international legitimacy of the United States following the Iraq War, Hierarchy in International Relations offers a powerful analytic perspective that has important implications for understanding America's position in the world in the years ahead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aInternational relations. 4aInternational Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Diplomacy.2bisacsh  aDiplomacy.  aHobbesian state of nature.  aInternational relations.  adeclining international legitimacy of the United States.  aforeign policies.  aforeign relations.  aglobal political economies.  ahandbook of international relations.  ainternational hierarchies.  ainternational politic students.  ainternational political theory.  ainternational politics strategy.  ainternational politics.  ainternational relations theory.  aintro to international relations.  alogics of hierarchy.  aorder in world politics.  apolitical authority.  apolitical economies.  apolitical nature of authority.  apolitical science .  apolitical science student.  apolitical science.  apolitical sovereignty.  apolitical theory .  apolitical theory.  apower and interdependence.  ascholars of international relations.  asocial theory of international politics.  asovereignty studies.  astudying american foreign policy.  astudying international politics.  astudying international relations.  atheory of international politics.  aunited states foreign policy.  aunited states foreign relations.  aworld political economy.  aworld politics.